A seven-year-old boy on Wednesday died from suspected food poisoning after eating mangoes in Kithumani village, Makueni. Makueni county police commander Joseph Ole Napeiyan said the boy, his parents and siblings developed stomach complications. Peter Nyamasyo died at Mbenuu Health Centre where he was taken after developing diarrhoea and vomiting. “They consumed mangoes harvested from their farm by the boy, who later started complaining of stomach upsets at around 2am,” Napeiyan said. “The family members began to vomit and diarrhoea, the deceased developed acute complications and was taken to the hospital.” The rest of the family members were treated and discharged in stable condition. Napeiyan said police have begun investigating the incident and asked residents to be patient as they try to unravel the cause of the death. The body was taken to Kilome Hospital mortuary awaiting postmortem. Edited by Kiilu Damaris